# Carrier Reference

This file is a template. Copy it to `Carrier_Reference.md` (or split into one file per carrier if you prefer), populate it with your real carriers and contacts, and delete this `.example` version.

The pattern below is for an independent group benefits advisor. Replace with your own carrier panel, products, and contacts.

---

## Sun Life

**Product lines I sell:** Group dental, EHC, basic life, dependent life, AD&D, optional life.

**Underwriter contact (small group, under 25 lives):** Marcy Tran, marcy.tran@sunlife.com, last spoke 2026-04-22. Direct phone available on request.

**Service rep:** Daniel Pham, daniel.pham@sunlife.com. Use for claims escalations, plan amendments, member changes.

**Claims experience:** Strong. Most paramedical claims process in 5 to 7 business days. Online portal is reliable. Members do not complain.

**Renewal pattern:** First quotes go out roughly 60 days before renewal. Negotiation room exists if loss ratio is under 70 percent. They will hold a renewal for two weeks past the date if you ask.

**What they are good at:** Dental, EHC, claims service. Member experience.

**What to watch out for:** AD&D base coverage is thin; the rider matters. Optional life requires medical underwriting at thresholds I sometimes forget; check before quoting.

**Last touched:** 2026-04-22.

---

## Canada Life

**Product lines I sell:** Group benefits (full suite), critical illness, disability.

**Underwriter contact (small group):** [populate with your actual contact]

**Service rep:** [populate]

**Claims experience:** Solid. Slower than Sun Life on paramedical, faster on disability.

**Renewal pattern:** Renewal letters arrive on time, rate increases tend to be aggressive in years 2 to 3 if the group has had any claims experience.

**What they are good at:** Critical illness, disability, larger groups.

**What to watch out for:** Their dental annual maximums are middle-of-pack; clients comparing on dental alone may be unhappy.

